    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a three-level hierarchy of sales distribution data (\u03bc=33.3, \u03c3=12.5) with intentional clustering in electronics sales. Synthetic values maintain proportional relationships between parent-child nodes (sum validation) while introducing natural variance through Poisson-distributed residuals. The treemap encoding follows Bertin's matrix theory - size represents sales volume while color intensity shows growth rate. Cairo's principles are implemented through size-color dual encoding and progressive disclosure via drilldown. The 'stripes' algorithm improves comparative analysis between sibling nodes compared to squarified layouts. Statistical validity is maintained through Z-score based color mapping (\u03c3=2.8) and quartile-based size bins."
